headline: SLB Earnings Beat Expectations. The Oil Services Stock Is Rising.
summary: STOCKSTOWATCHTODAY BLOG   SLB the oilfield services provider, beat analysts’ expectations for second-quarter earnings amid a prolonged slump in oil prices. The stock rose. The Houston-based company formerly known as Schlumberger said that adjusted earnings-per-share came in at 74 cents, down 4% from a year ago.
